==English==

===Etymology===
The phrase is derived from the territorial behaviour of certain animals, such as male cats, which mark territorial claims with urine.

===Noun===
'''[[pissing]] [[war]]'''

# An often vicious conflict in which combatants contend for dominance over certain territory.
# A [[pissing contest]]
# An ideological or nonphysical conflict 
#: ''We didn't do any press because we were just going to get in a pissing war [...]'' -- Matt Stone, [http://www.cnn.com/2006/SHOWBIZ/TV/07/14/television.southpark.reut/index.html?section=cnn_latest]
#: ''The other two [...] are in a righter-than-thou pissing war'' -- Geov Parrish, [http://www.workingforchange.com/article.cfm?ItemID=15638]

===Usage notes===
May be considered vulgar.